  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gs_sec2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2. `add_onsite!` — on-site potential\n",
    "\n",
    "`add_onsite!(H, f)` adds a diagonal term $V_i = f(i)$ (1-indexed) via a 1D QTCI-compressed\n",
    "diagonal MPO.  All Chebyshev caches are automatically invalidated.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here: linear tilt $V(i) = U_0(i/N - 0.5)$ breaks particle-hole symmetry."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "gs_onsite",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "H_on = TensorBinding.get_Hamiltonian(\"chain_1d\", 1.0; L=L)\n",
    "U0   = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "TensorBinding.add_onsite!(H_on, i -> U0 * (i / H_on.N - 0.5))\n",
    "\n",
    "TensorBinding.KPM_Tn(H_on, Ncheb; maxdim=mdim)\n",
    "three_panel(H_on, omega; Ncheb=Ncheb, mdim=mdim, title_prefix=\"+ onsite tilt\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gs_sec3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. `add_hopping!` — generic (NNN) hopping\n",
    "\n",
    "`add_hopping!(H, f)` compresses the full `N x N` matrix `f(i,j)` into an MPO via QTCI\n",
    "and adds it to `H`.  Works for any range and any site-dependence.\n",
    "\n",
    "Here: second-nearest-neighbour hopping $t_2$, dispersion\n",
    "$\\varepsilon(k) = -2t_1\\cos k - 2t_2\\cos 2k$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "gs_hopping",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "H_nnn = TensorBinding.get_Hamiltonian(\"chain_1d\", 1.0; L=L)\n",
    "t2    = 0.4\n",
    "TensorBinding.add_hopping!(H_nnn, (i, j) -> abs(i - j) == 2 ? -t2 : 0.0;\n",
    "                            type=Float64)\n",
    "\n",
    "omega_nnn = range(-6.0, 6.0; length=120)\n",
    "TensorBinding.KPM_Tn(H_nnn, Ncheb; maxdim=mdim)\n",
    "three_panel(H_nnn, omega_nnn; Ncheb=Ncheb, mdim=mdim, title_prefix=\"+ NNN t2=$(t2)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gs_sec4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4. `add_zeeman!` — spin-1/2 + Zeeman field\n",
    "\n",
    "`add_zeeman!(H, h; direction=:z)` automatically prepends a spin-1/2 index\n",
    "(calling `add_spin!` internally) and adds $h S_z$.  The site chain becomes\n",
    "`[spin_s, pos_qubits...]` and the physical Hilbert space doubles.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Zeeman field lifts the spin degeneracy, splitting every band into two branches\n",
    "separated by $h$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "gs_zeeman",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "H_z = TensorBinding.get_Hamiltonian(\"chain_1d\", 1.0; L=L)\n",
    "h_z = 1.5\n",
    "TensorBinding.add_zeeman!(H_z, h_z; direction=:z)\n",
    "\n",
    "omega_z = range(-5.0, 5.0; length=120)\n",
    "TensorBinding.KPM_Tn(H_z, Ncheb; maxdim=mdim)\n",
    "three_panel(H_z, omega_z; Ncheb=Ncheb, mdim=mdim, title_prefix=\"+ Zeeman h=$(h_z)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gs_sec5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5. `add_soc!` — Rashba spin-orbit coupling\n",
    "\n",
    "`add_soc!(H, lambda; type=:rashba)` adds the 1D Rashba term\n",
    "$\\lambda(S_y K_+ - S_y K_-)$ where $K_\\pm$ are shift MPOs.\n",
    "Combined with the Zeeman field, this opens a gap at the band crossing\n",
    "and produces a spin-helical state."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "gs_soc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "H_soc = TensorBinding.get_Hamiltonian(\"chain_1d\", 1.0; L=L)\n",
    "TensorBinding.add_zeeman!(H_soc, 1.0; direction=:z)\n",
    "TensorBinding.add_soc!(H_soc, 0.5; type=:rashba)\n",
    "\n",
    "omega_soc = range(-5.0, 5.0; length=120)\n",
    "TensorBinding.KPM_Tn(H_soc, Ncheb; maxdim=mdim)\n",
    "three_panel(H_soc, omega_soc; Ncheb=Ncheb, mdim=mdim, title_prefix=\"+ Zeeman + Rashba\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "gs_sec6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. `add_superconductivity!` — spinless s-wave BdG\n",
    "\n",
    "`add_superconductivity!(H, Delta; type=:swave)` extends `H` to Nambu space:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$H_{\\rm BdG} = \\tau_z \\otimes H + \\tau_+ \\Delta + \\tau_- \\Delta^\\dagger$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The spectrum has exact particle-hole symmetry ($\\pm E$ pairs).\n",
    "A superconducting gap of size $\\sim 2|\\Delta|$ opens at $\\omega = 0$."
   ]
  },
